Uasin Gishu Governor Jackson Mandago (pictured) yesterday warned vandals against destroying street lights. He said they were put up so traders could do b usiness at night without fear of attack. ”I am warning people with bad behaviour that their days are numbered. I cannot allow someone to destroy streetlights that we have used millions of shillings to install,” he said in Eldoret town yesterday. Mandago said security lights along Langas have been destroyed and urged residents to report vandals to police. “I promise to take action. Culprits will face te law,” the governor said.